  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) Šarrukin , king of Agade , commissioner of Inana , king of the world , išib priest of An , king of the Land , chief governor of Enlil , conquered the city of Unug and demolished its city-walls . He fought with the leader of Unug and defeated him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.21",
      "line_range": "21",
      "translation": "(21) He fought with Lugal-zagesi , king of Unug , captured him , and took him to the gate of Enlil in a neck stock ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.30",
      "line_range": "30",
      "translation": "(30) Šarrukin , king of Agade , fought with the leader of Urim and defeated him . He conquered his city and demolished its city-walls ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.42",
      "line_range": "42",
      "translation": "(42) He conquered the temple of Ninmarki , and demolished its walls . From Lagaš until the sea he conquered all lands , all of them , and washed his weapons in the sea ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.53",
      "line_range": "53",
      "translation": "(53) He fought with the leader of Umma and defeated him . He conquered his city and demolished its city-walls ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.62",
      "line_range": "62",
      "translation": "(62) Enlil made Šarrukin , king of the Land , a man without opponent , and gave him ( all the people ) from the Upper sea to the Lower sea . From the Lower sea the citizen of Agade exercized rulership ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.81",
      "line_range": "81",
      "translation": "(81) Mari and Elam stood ( in obedience ) before Šarrukin , king of the Land . Šarrukin , king of the Land , restored Kiš , and the city provided him with ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.94",
      "line_range": "94",
      "translation": "(94) Whoever obliterates this inscription , may Utu uproot him and destroy his lineage !"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000834.103",
      "line_range": "103",
      "translation": "(colophon 1, 1) The inscription on its socle ."
    }
  ],
